package.description:
This package implements a very simple VisTrails module called PythonCalc. This is intended as a simple example that can be referred to by users to create their own packages and modules later.
If you're interested in developing new modules for VisTrails, you should also consult the documentation in the User's Guide and in core/modules/vistrails_module.py.
package.name: PythonCalc

package.description: HTTP provides packages for HTTP-based file fetching. This provides a location-independent way of referring to files. This package uses a local cache of the files, inside the per-user VisTrails directory. This way, files that haven't been changed do not need downloading. The check is performed efficiently using the HTTP GET headers.
package.name: HTTP

package.description:
Matplotlib package for VisTrails.
This package wrap Matplotlib to provide a plotting tool for VisTrails. We are going to use the 'Qt4Agg' backend of the library.
package.name: matplotlib
